benedetta faedi the clayman institute for gender research skip to main content standford university the clayman institute for gender research the clayman institute for gender research home programs news strategic focus events about research fellowships library media center gender news no news found events no events found you are here home people benedetta faedi benedetta faedi graduate dissertation fellow 2008 09 law benedetta faedi is a doctoral candidate at stanford law school and her main fields of research are gender legal issues and human rights her dissertation investigates practices of sexual violence against girls and women in haiti and the incentives conditions and decision making processes fostering them to join armed groups and become perpetrators of violence themselves ultimately this analysis aims at envisaging potential strategies and effective measures that international legal institutions could implement to increase women's involvement at the grassroots level in the reconciliation of the community as well as in official conflict resolution processes donate make a donation social links facebook twitter youtube scribd contact serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 8640 map 650 723 1994 gender email stanford edu
